PiggyVest, a savings and investment platform, says over N242 billion was paid to 3.5 million customers in 2021. Somto Ifezua, chief executive officer, PiggyVest, disclosed this in a newsletter released on Sunday. “For the past 5 and a half years, my amazing team and I have been committed to building a product that truly benefits you. It’s not been an easy task making sure everyone is happy, but we are grateful for the opportunity and we never take it for granted,” Ifezue said. “It’s not been an easy task making sure everyone is happy, but we are grateful for the opportunity and we never take it for granted. “With over 3.5 million customers and over ₦242 billion Naira successfully paid out in 2021 alone, we are once again saying thank you for trusting us.” Ifezue said customers should expect the platform to be more productive as they work on innovations. “We are overhauling our app to make much more user friendly & secure. We are bringing loads of investment opportunities for you via Investify. Better & faster customer support. More features to help you in your financial journey. Our continued commitment lies in the complete satisfaction of each and every PiggyVest user”. Piggyvest is an automated savings platform that helps customers invest spare money with promises of interest rates.